quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  22,56,"The dominion (or sovereignty) on that day shall be AllahÂ´s, He shall judge between them; and those who believe and do aright shall be in Gardens of Delight"
  22,57,"But those who disbelieve and deny Our revelation, for them is a shameful doom"
  22,58,"And those who flee their homes in the cause of Allah, and then are slain or die, Allah will surely provide them with a goodly provision; for, verily, Allah is the best of providers"
  22,59,"Assuredly, He shall make them enter by an entrance that they will love. For, verily, Allah is Knower, Most-forbearing"
  22,60,"That is so. Whoever retaliates with the like of what He has been made to suffer, and shall then be wronged again, Allah shall surely succour him; verily, Allah blots out sins and is constantly Forgiving"
  22,61,"That is because Allah causes the night to pass into day, and causes the day to pass into night, and because Allah is Hearer, Seer"
  22,62,"That is because Allah, He is the Truth (or Reality), and that whereon they call instead of Him is the False, and because Allah, He is the High, the Great"
  22,63,"See you not how Allah sends down water from the sky, and on the morrow the earth is green? Verily, Allah is Subtile, Aware"
  22,64,"Unto Him belongs all that is in the heavens and that is in the earth; verily, Allah is the Absolute, the Owner of all Praise"